HEADWORD: Parvoline
<hw>Par"vo*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A liquid base, <chform>C9H13N</chform>, of the pyridine group,
found in coal tar; also, any one of the series of isomeric substances of
which it is the type.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

